text.tspan: Nigerians usually use right hands because is considered a sign of disrespect to greet, eat, hand over, or
collect things from people with your left hand. Considering Brazilian culture we could say that:
Os nigerianos geralmente usam a mão direita porque é considerado um sinal de desrespeito cumprimentar, comer entregar ou
